content.description: Up chossy corner. Stem out left onto vertical face over roof and clip bolt. Crazy climbing past two more bols lead to the anchors on the top. Bad rock but lots of fun.
content.protection: Pro on the bottom 3 bolts on the top
content.location: This route is on the left side of the cliff.  It is located to the right of Pink medusa. also to the right of a 2 bolt project.

content.description: Despite the choss, this route is so steep it has to be classic.  Totally wild.
content.location: This route is just to the right of Clicking Barnackles.

content.description: This one is a nice looking line and looks deceptively easy.  Many have backed down due to the high first bolt. A combination of friction footwork and balancey side pulls makes this a great route and a hard 9.  A cam can be placed low on the route if desired for a more tolerable first clip.
content.protection: Sport. One medium cam down low if desired. It's also possible to pre-clip the first bolt.
content.location: On the Left side of the wall.  Just to the right of Spawning Effort.  It's the only climb on the wall that looks like a slab route.

content.description: Start up the right-facing corner and climb up to the roofs, then angle rightward to anchors. Top half is a friction climb.
content.location: Between Julia the Viking Queen and Clicking the Barnacles.

content.description: This route starts on a small ledge, leads to a bear hug, then mantle, and on to a ledge under roof. Goes left and over to face and the top.
content.protection: pro to 1/2, 3 bolts, chains on top

content.description: Start the climb just about in the center of the cliff directly below two red pieces of webbing at the top.  climb over nose then wedge your way over a overhang to a dirty ledge, then srtaight ip the face with little pincher holds.
content.protection: has fixed bolts and anchors at top. Could use some small nuts in the beginning.

content.description: Recently (re?)bolted. Currently, this is the easiest lead in Bellingham. The route starts in a dihedral and finishes on a ledge below the roof.
content.protection: Two bolts to an old quarter inch and new glue-in for an anchor.
content.location: Just right of Pink Medusa (which is the route furthest left).

content.description: Starts off same bolt as for Saffron Spider, but goes right till level or just below right slanting diagonal shallow cracks leading to stance below bulge. Move right over nose and up.
content.protection: 8 bolts total. Most new stainless steal wave bolt glue ins. Permanent stainless steel clip anchors at top. No trad gear required. One can stick clip the first bolt.

content.description: This is an extension to "Clicking Barnacles". Clip anchor, and continue through the roof. Follow glue-in bolts up and left to the top of the cliff. Very fun and interesting movement through the crux. Bolts were donated by the same doctor who removed a siding nail from my thigh the day after the first ascent.
content.location: Starts where approach trail meets the cliff. "Clicking Barnacles" has distinct honeycomb shaped pockets just above the first bolt.

content.description: Again use same bolt start, but right under roof, past fp then over roof and...open project
This Route stays fairly dry even on rainy days. Lay back or stem up the finger crack to the first bolt. Exciting jugs and sidepulls await as you traverse this beauty!
content.protection: Sport 5 bolts. plus anchor cold shuts at top
content.location: This one is The traverse under the big roof. And Is in the center of the wall. This route crosses Pale Young Eels.

content.description: Clip the first bolt of Saffron Spider then veer right and into a right facing dihedral to the anchors. There is a scary looking piton along the way but i have witnessed a decent fall on it, small pro is also an option if preferred.
content.location: On left side of wall.  Shares the first bolt with Saffron Spider then heads into the right facing dihedral.

content.description: This is a great route that requires some interesting moves to get over a slight bulge.  Good holds leave one feeling like a monkey.
content.protection: 3 bolts. Two cold shuts at top to rap off of.
content.location: This is the right most climb on the wall.

content.description: Climbs over bubbly rock and finishes on huge holds. An instant classic.  This route stays dry pretty much all the time.
content.location: This route shares an anchor with Julia the Viking Queen.  Look for the route that goes straight up to the anchor just under the roof.  This is where the trail comes into the wall.

content.description: Fun moves off the boulder to the top of the pillar. Clip a bolt in the roof and harness your qi for the roof crux. A variety of kung fu styles are used to surmount the roof and reach a slab alcove. Step left, crossing Grog Supply, and continue up a short crack. Continue up and left to the prominent arete clipping glue-in-bolts to the top of the wall and a chain anchor.
content.protection: glue-in-bolts, permadraw at the lip of the roof
content.location: Left from where the trail meets the cliff. Right of slab and "Saffron Spider". Starts under roof from a flat topped boulder at the base of a distinct 10' pillar.
